<p>Alsatian pastor J.G. Stuber composed this puzzle canon in the late 18th century.</p>
<p>&#8220;It was always a great delight to me, in riding my horse from one village to another, to hear in the fields and among the heights the melodies which I had taught,&#8221; <a href="https://ia804608.us.archive.org/1/items/lifeofjeanfrede00butl/lifeofjeanfrede00butl.pdf#page=60">he wrote</a>. &#8220;I could often distinguish very beautiful and harmonious voices.&#8221;</p>
